  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19: inclusive education and digital environments</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As an immediate response to the COVID-19 outbreak, the project aims to provide educational leaders, administrators and teachers with concrete knowledge and skills as well as appropriate tools and resources to make education more accessible and inclusive to all learners. A special attention will be placed on the application of the Open and Distance Learning as one of the most sustainable methods for overcoming the educational barriers faced by persons with disabilities during the emergency situations. The ODL is also considered to be a more sustainable method for overcoming the educational barriers in a long term. The inter-sectoral project will be implemented by CI, SHS, ED and IIEP.</narrative>
  </description>
